# Final Advice

Do not try to “finish books.”

That is the biggest beginner mistake.

Instead:

* read chapters relevant to project
* watch IIT/NPTEL lectures
* implement small simulations
* connect concepts slowly
* revisit books repeatedly

Wireless communication becomes beautiful only after gradual exposure.

At first it feels abstract.

Then suddenly:

* OFDM
* FFT
* fading
* pilots
* CSI
* channel estimation

all connect together like one engineering ecosystem.


